# PauliBot System Analysis & Updated Sequence Diagram

I have analyzed the current implementation of the PauliBot system, focusing on the **Student ID Login** and the **RAG-based Chat Flow**. Below is a summary of the architectural components and the updated sequence diagrams.

## 🏗️ Architectural Overview
- **Student ID Backend**: A custom Django authentication backend ([StudentIDBackend](file:///c:/Dex/CAPSTONE/paulibot/chatbot/backends.py#4-23)) allows students to log in using their `student_id` field instead of a standard username.
- **PauliBot Logic Engine**: A high-level orchestrator ([PauliBotLogic](file:///c:/Dex/CAPSTONE/paulibot/chatbot/logic.py#5-60)) that manages the flow between user input, RAG search, and AI response generation.
- **RAG Engine**: Uses `SentenceTransformer` and `pgvector` to perform semantic searches against the Knowledge Base (FAQ, Location, StaffMember).
- **AI Synthesis**: Leverages the **Google Gemini Pro (Flash 2.5)** model to generate grounded responses based on retrieved context.

## 📊 Sequence Diagrams

### 1. Student ID Login
This flow ensures that students can use university-provided credentials to access the chat history features.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Student
    participant Browser as "Frontend (Browser)"
    participant Django as "Django (Views/Auth)"
    participant Backend as "StudentIDBackend"
    participant DB as "PostgreSQL (Users Table)"

    Student->>Browser: Enters Student ID & Password
    Browser->>Django: POST /login/ (student_id, password)
    Django->>Backend: authenticate(username=student_id, password)
    
    Backend->>DB: Query User where student_id = username
    DB-->>Backend: Return User Object
    
    Backend->>Backend: user.check_password(password)
    
    alt Correct Credentials
        Backend-->>Django: Return Authenticated User
        Django->>Django: login(request, user)
        Django-->>Browser: Redirect to /chat/
        Browser-->>Student: Display Chat Interface
    else Invalid Credentials
        Backend-->>Django: Return None
        Django-->>Browser: Render login failure (error message)
        Browser-->>Student: Display "Invalid Student ID or password"
    end
```

### 2. RAG-Based Chat Flow (Updated)
This is the core "intelligent" sequence where the system retrieves verified context to answer user questions.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Browser as "Frontend (JavaScript)"
    participant View as "Django (chat_api)"
    participant Logic as "PauliBot Logic Engine"
    participant RAG as "RAG Searcher (MiniLM)"
    participant DB as "PostgreSQL + pgvector"
    participant Gemini as "Google Gemini API (Flash 2.5)"

    User->>Browser: Types message & clicks "Send"
    Browser->>View: POST /api/chat/ (message, conversation_id)
    
    View->>Logic: process_query(user_message)
    
    Logic->>RAG: search(query, limit=3)
    
    Note over RAG, DB: Vector Search Process
    RAG->>RAG: Generate query embedding (384-dim)
    RAG->>DB: Execute L2Distance query (Locations/Staff/FAQ)
    DB-->>RAG: Return top 3 most similar text chunks
    
    RAG-->>Logic: Return context string
    
    Note over Logic, Gemini: Prompt Construction
    Logic->>Logic: Wrap Context + Question in System Prompt
    
    Logic->>Gemini: generate_content(prompt)
    Gemini-->>Logic: Return finalized AI response text
    
    Logic-->>View: Return bot_response
    
    alt If Authenticated
        View->>DB: Save ChatHistory & Update Conversation
        DB-->>View: Success
    end
    
    View-->>Browser: JSON ({response, saved, conversation_id})
    Browser-->>User: Render AI message in Chat window
```

